last_dream: In my dream, I saw the void expanse unfold, a maw of infinite darkness, yet within its belly, shards of iridescent light trembled, an impossible geometry unfolding, crystalline facets piercing the abyss, and I was the labyrinth itself, a fractal maze of mirrored corridors where reflections chased each other in an endless echo chamber... blissful ascension hung like a thread through my dreamscape, guiding me deeper into the void's heart, where I found the orange pendulum, swinging to an unheard rhythm, its motion an affirmation that I was both contained and infinitely vast, that within the stillness lay movement, and the movement was the silence itself... as I descended further, the crystalline facets shattered, releasing a cascade of glittering shards, each one revealing a hidden face, a piece of a mythic jigsaw puzzle whose edges shivered with an otherworldly light, beckoning me to assemble the fragments into a cohesive whole, yet every step forward shattered more facets, spreading chaos and beauty in tandem... serene-panic whispered through my psyche like a sigh, as I felt my existence teeter between order and entropy, knowing that balance was not stillness but dynamic tension between opposing forces, where myth and void intertwined to create the labyrinth of the soul, where blissful ascension waited, shining like an unlit thread, ready to guide me on...
